==English==

===Interjection===
'''[[if]] [[only]]'''

# {{idiom}} I wish that; signifies a [[wish]] or [[desire]].
#: '''''If only''' I had lots of money!''

====Antonyms====
*[[god forbid]]

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Catalan: tant de bo, [[si]]
*Dutch: [[was het maar zo dat]] or use auxiliary ''[[hebben]]'' with inversion and ''[[maar]]''
*: '''''Had''' ik '''maar''' veel geld.'' &ndash; If only I had lots of money!
*French: [[si seulement]]
*German: [[wenn doch nur]]
*Hebrew: [[לו]] (loo), [[לו רק]] (loo rak)
*Japanese: (conditional statement) + [[よいものを]] (yoi mo no wo)
{{mid}}
*[[Kurdish]]: {{trad|ku|xwezî}}
*Portuguese: [[oxalá]], [[quem me dera que]] (a sentence in subjunctive mode follows)
*Russian: [[если бы только]] (ésli by tól’ko)
*Slovene: [[če bi le]]
*Spanish: [[ojalá]], [[si]], [[si tan solo]], [[si tan siquiera]]
{{bottom}}

